{
  "text": "2) Online dictionary learning Although the offline DL stage has adjust the overcomplete basis according the training data, it is impossible to be fit for all kinds of time-varying interference patterns. Moreover, its computation load is quite large for realtime localization. On the contrary, the online incremental learning is especially applicable when one seeks to find the variation in the sense that the time-varying channels pattern might not be specifically learned offline but can be distinguished from the past online observations. Based on the incremental learning pattern, the online learning algorithm in [CITATION_1] can use the result of the offline DL stage as a warm restart for computing the next dictionary where the new samples will be fed into the online dictionary learning procedure, and thus a single iteration has empirically been found to be enough [CITATION_2] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
